b'' b'' b'i wonder if anybody know of a x-window-based postscript file' b'viewer that runs under sunos (prefered), hpux, or ibm aix.' b"reason i'm looking for this utility is that i've downloaded these" b"large postscript documents and i'd like to know how useful (and how" b'long) they are before commiting them to the printer and potentially' b'wasting pages of paper and hogging the printer for hour.' b'' b'' b'get ghostscript and ghostview. ghostview is a postscript previewer' b'that uses ghostscript.' b'' b'from the ghostview readme:' b'' b'' b'' b'ghostview an x11 user interface for ghostscript.' b'' b'ghostview is full function user interface for ghostscript b'' b'brief list of features:' b"- ghostview parses any known version of adobe's document structuring" b'conventions.' b'- page size is automatically determined from the document structuring' b'comments. the user is able to override the values from the comments.' b'- window size is set to the bounding box for encapsulated postscript figures.' b'- default page size is letter and can be changed via xresources or' b'application defaults file to a4 (or any other valid size) for our' b'european friends.' b'- scrollbars appear when necessary.' b'- page orientation is automatically determined from the document structuring' b'comments. the user is able to override the values from the comments.' b'- ability to view at orientations: portrait, landscape, upside-down,' b'and seascape (for those who rotate landscape the other direction).' b'- ability to preview in any supported visual. (can preview in gray-scale' b'or color on a color monitor.)' b'- ability to mark pages for printing, or saving. (good for people that' b'printed a page document and lost page due to a printer jam.)' b'- can popup zoom windows at printer resolution' b'(1 display dot printer dot).' b'' b'the ghostview distribution includes a ghostview widget that people' b'are encouraged to use in other programs.' b'' b'ghostview-1.3 is available via anonymous ftp from:' b'prep.ai.mit.edu:/pub/gnu/ghostview-1.3.tar.z' b'appenzell.cs.wisc.edu:/pub/ghostview-1.3.tar.z' b'' b'' b'from the ghostscript readme:' b'' b'*****************************************************' b'* this file describes version of ghostscript. b'*****************************************************' b'' b'********' b'******** an overview of ghostscript b'********' b'' b'ghostscript is the name of a set of software that provides:' b'' b'- an interpreter for the ghostscript language, which very' b'closely resembles the postscript (tm) language; and' b'' b'- a set of c procedures (the ghostscript library) that' b'implement the graphics capabilities that appear as primitive' b'operations in the ghostscript language.' b'' b'the ghostscript language interpreter and library are written entirely' b'in c, with some assembly-language accelerators for ms-dos platforms.' b'currently, ghostscript is known to run on the following platform' b'families:' b'' b'- ibm pc and compatibles with ega, vga, supervga, or compatible' b'graphics under ms-dos or b'' b'- a wide variety of unix systems using x windows version b'release and including sun-3, sun-4, sun-386i,' b'sun sparcstation generic machines running 386/ix;' b'h-p and decstation and vax' b'running ultrix; sequent symmetry; convex c1 and c2;' b'tektronix sgi iris indigo;' b'' b'- sun workstations (sun-3, sparc, sun-386i) running sunview;' b'' b'- vax, vms with x11r3/4/5, gcc and dec c compiler (dec c compiler' b'version or later is required).' b'' b'' b'(get ghostscript from the same ftp site you get ghostview.)' b'' b'--' b'tim williams com: b'night vision electronic sensors directorate dsn: b'amsel-rd-nv-vispd (williams) fax: 